55
00:04:48,569 --> 00:04:52,209
222 squadron.
After what seemed like a never-ending period

56
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:57,599
of leading the squadron in aerobatics, formation
flying and routine patrols, Bader’s first

57
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:02,050
engagement with the enemy in the Second World
War came over Dunkirk.

58
00:05:02,050 --> 00:05:08,860
His first kill was a Messerschmitt 109, shooting
