59
00:05:08,860 --> 00:05:14,830
patrols in Dunkirk were uneventful for Bader.
After that he was promoted again and given

60
00:05:14,829 --> 00:05:21,430
his own squadron, 242. It was a Canadian squadron,
the only one in the RAF, and he was their

61
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:27,389
new squadron leader, flying Hurricanes again.
With his discipline and his tendency to lead

62
00:05:27,389 --> 00:05:33,339
from the front, Bader soon had the squadron
