18 Hurricanes intercepted over 100 German

67
00:05:55,019 --> 00:06:01,159
aircraft, mainly bombers. In the ensuing battle,
Bader registered two kills and the squadron

68
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:06,620
had downed 12 aircraft in total, without any
damage to a single Hurricane.

69
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:11,680
Bader discussed and tried out new tactics
for the air battle. He came up with a new

70
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:16,660
formation, where five squadrons would fly
together, called “12 Group Wing”.

71
00:06:16,660 --> 00:06:21,630
The wing was a success and they managed 52
kills in one day at their peak. Bader was

72
00:06:21,629 --> 00:06:27,800
awarded the Distinguished Service Order medal.
When the Battle of Britain was over, the 12

73
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:35,090
Group Wing had shot down 152 enemies whilst
losing 30 of their own pilots. By the end

74
00:06:35,089 --> 00:06:40,060
of 1940, 242 squadron had one DSO and nine
