98
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:39,799
and descended on them after clambering out
the window.

99
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:44,370
After meeting the couple’s son, he was taken
to the nearby French family home but was discovered

100
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:48,009
by the Germans hiding in the shed when they
came to search the property.

101
00:08:48,009 --> 00:08:53,588
This time the Germans took no chances. They
took Bader’s metal legs and drove him to

102
00:08:53,589 --> 00:08:57,250
Brussels, where he was put on a train and
guarded whilst it travelled to Germany.

103
00:08:57,250 --> 00:09:02,750
Bader spent the next few months in various
prisoner of war camps. One of the largest

104
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:09,360
